    "created_at": "2015-08-19T20:39:30Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-08-19T20:39:30Z",
    "body": "If you want to change the title to some translated text, you can do that with the current release.\nIt turns out the current implementation extends `alert` and `confirm` with a second parameter. If you set it to a non empty string, that string will be displayed as the title of the dialog. For example `alert(\"I am an alert box!\", \"Foobar\");` will show the title `Foobar`.\n\nI know it's not exactly what you wanted but I thought it might still help you.\n"
